<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 13 at 4:36PM CDT  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Claiborne, southwestern Hinds and northwestern Copiah Counties
through 515 PM CDT...
At 436 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rocky Springs, or 21 miles south of Vicksburg, moving northeast at 40
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Carpenter around 450 PM CDT.
Utica around 500 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for central and
southwestern Mississippi.</instruction>
